cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a learning-based method for vehicle-to-infrastructure communication in vehicular networks.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed method uses a sequence-to-sequence neural network for online inference.
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with channel acquisition and beam training overhead reduction.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a machine learning-based approach.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper deals with optimizing the beamforming process in vehicular networks.
